				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\varepsilon _c.$$\end{document} Due to charmed hadrons having shorter lifetimes and smaller masses than b-hadrons, the identification of charm jets is challenging, and the efficiency of the optimal operating point tends be much lower than for b-tagging.

